<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.1457029>
    dc:description "FIGURES 14–15. Zeugophora (Pedrillia) dimorpha Gressitt, 1945. 14. Dorsal view; 15, Paratype deposited in CAS, dorsal side. Scale line = 2.0 mm (Fig. 14)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/1457029/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.1457025>
    dc:description "FIGURES 5–6. Frons, anterior view. 5. Zeugophora (Zeugophora) ancora Reitter, 1900 from Ningxia (China), female, circle indicating concave on centre of frons; 6. Zeugophora (Pedrillia) yunnanica (Chen & Pu, 1962) from Yunnan (China), arrow indicating frontal suture. Scale line = 0.5 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/1457025/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.1457035>
    dc:description "FIGURES 26–29. Type of Zeugophora (Pedrillia) longicornis Westwood, 1864. 26. Type of Z. (P.) longicornis on the same plate, dorsal; 27. Label; 28–29, Type of Z. (P.) longicornis. Scale line = 2.0 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/1457035/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.1457037>
    dc:description "FIGURES 30–32.Type of Zeugophora (Pedrillia) bicoloriventris Pic, 1911. 30. Label; 31. Dorsal view; 32. Lateral view. Scale line = 2.0 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/1457037/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

